description: jpx-accounting project rules (cross-tool contract lives in AGENTS.md)
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `AGENTS.md` first — it is the cross-tool agent contract (JPx ADR DL-001) and wins on
conflict. `CLAUDE.md` carries the deep project memory; `docs/CONVENTIONS.md` the 28
incident-derived rules.

Non-negotiables while editing here:

- Append-only ledger events; never rewrite history. The review queue is the only path to a
  posted voucher — AI output executes nothing without explicit human approval.
- Keep `MemoryLedgerStore` and `PostgresLedgerStore` behavior-identical; shared logic goes
  in `packages/domain`.
- `packages/contracts` (Zod v4) is the single source of truth for API shapes — change the
  schema first, then both stores, then the UI.
- Every `messages/en.json` key needs its `sv.json` twin.
- `@dnd-kit` only in `sortable-grid.tsx`; `ai`/`@ai-sdk` only under `components/advisor/` +
  `services/api/src/advisor/`; recharts only via the reports lazy barrel.
- Windows shell: prepend `$env:LOCALAPPDATA\corepack-shims` to PATH before any pnpm call.
- Gate before merge: `pnpm check`, then E2E via `pnpm build:e2e` (never plain build), then
  visual diffs reviewed before any `--update-snapshots`.
